      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the very embers of my soul. How cruel it is, that after all the vows whispered under the willow trees, I am left with nothing but this hollow ache. The world has become a cold, grey shroud, and I find I no longer have the strength to tear it away. It feels as though the darkness is not merely around me, but within me, calling me to finally, peacefully, cease to be.",
